Clinical Recommendations: 
Men's Health Recommendations: Please report any new worrying urinary symptoms to your doctor.
Women's Health Recommendations: 
Overview Notes: A raised urea with normal kidney function suggests dehydration which is not surprising post JHB to Sea cycle race. Make sure you are drinking at least 2 litres of water a day and more when cycling.
Comment Key: MensHealthNote
Comment Value: None
Special Investigation Notes: Nil

Overview Notes: A raised urea with normal kidney function suggests dehydration which is not surprising post JHB to Sea cycle race. Make sure you are drinking at least 2 litres of water a day and more when cycling.
Comment Key: MentalHealthAnxietyRecommendation
